# Salesforce Best Practices

## Component Structure
- Keep components small and focused on a single responsibility
- Use meaningful component names that describe their purpose
- Follow Pascal case for component names (e.g., MyComponent)
- Place components in appropriate directories based on their functionality

## JavaScript
- Use ES6+ features appropriately
- Avoid using global variables
- Implement error handling for all asynchronous operations
- Use meaningful variable and method names
- Keep methods small and focused

## HTML/Template
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Follow accessibility guidelines (WCAG 2.1)
- Keep template logic simple
- Use data binding appropriately

## CSS
- Use BEM naming convention for CSS classes
- Avoid using !important
- Keep styles modular and component-specific
- Use SLDS design tokens for consistency

## Performance
- Minimize the use of framework features that impact performance
- Implement lazy loading where appropriate
- Optimize render cycles
- Cache results when possible

## Testing
- Write unit tests for all components
- Test both positive and negative scenarios
- Mock external dependencies
- Maintain test coverage above 75%

